    <region regionID="IT-57-MC-01">
      <name>Appennino Fabrianese</name>
    </region>
    <dangerRating>
      <mainValue>considerable</mainValue>
      <validTimePeriod>all_day</validTimePeriod>
    </dangerRating>
    <avalancheProblem>
      <problemType>wind_slab</problemType>
      <elevation uom="m"/>
      <aspect>NE</aspect>
      <aspect>SW</aspect>
      <aspect>N</aspect>
      <aspect>W</aspect>
      <aspect>E</aspect>
      <aspect>NW</aspect>
      <aspect>SE</aspect>
      <aspect>S</aspect>
      <validTimePeriod>all_day</validTimePeriod>
      <snowpackStability>poor</snowpackStability>
      <frequency>some</frequency>
      <avalancheSize>3</avalancheSize>
    </avalancheProblem>
    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>New snow and wind slabs in all aspects. Wind slabs are to be evaluated with care and prudence.</highlights>
      <comment>As a consequence of new snow and a strong to storm force northeasterly wind, sometimes large wind slabs formed by the evening in particular in places that are protected from the wind. High-altitude starting zones have been replenished further quickly. In all aspects medium-sized slab avalanches are possible as a consequence of the snowfall. In particular on wind-loaded slopes the avalanches can be released in deep layers of the snowpack and reach large size.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>The old snowpack is moist. The wind slabs must be evaluated with care and prudence.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
    <travelAdvisory/>
    <tendency>
      <tendencyType>steady</tendencyType>
      <validTime>
        <startTime>2026-03-29T23:00:00Z</startTime>
        <endTime>2026-03-30T23:00:00Z</endTime>
